### [2 Kings (2 Samuel) Chapter 24](../../../bib/kjv/sa2024.htm#001.md)

[2 Kings (2 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa2001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa2 24:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa2 24:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa2024.htm#001.md), David, tempted by Satan,
forces Joab to number the people; [Sa2
24:5](../../../bib/kjv/sa2024.htm#005.md), The captains, in nine months and
twenty days, bring the muster of thirteen hundred thousand fighting men;
[Sa2 24:10](../../../bib/kjv/sa2024.htm#010.md), David repents, and having
three plagues propounded by God, chooses the three days' pestilence;
[Sa2 24:15](../../../bib/kjv/sa2024.htm#015.md), After the death of three
score and ten thousand, David by prayer prevents the destruction of
Jerusalem; [Sa2 24:18](../../../bib/kjv/sa2024.htm#018.md), David, by God's
direction, purchases Araunah's threshing floor; where having sacrificed,
the plague stays.

